12:01.372 --> 12:04.462
PLURALIZING THE MARRIAGE
WAS HEATHER HUNDIN,

12:04.506 --> 12:06.334
A RENOWNED PET PSYCHOLOGIST

12:06.377 --> 12:10.338
AND HOST OF THE WEEKLY
RADIO SHOW "DOGGONIT."

12:10.381 --> 12:12.906
SIMONE HUNDIN
WAS HAROLD'S THIRD WIFE.

12:12.949 --> 12:15.560
SHE PIONEERED K-18 OBEDIENCE,

12:15.604 --> 12:18.955
WHERE DEMANDING DOG OWNERS
GOT DOUBLE FROM THEIR CANINES.

12:18.999 --> 12:20.870
BANG, BANG, BANG.

12:20.914 --> 12:23.003
Narrator: LIKE THE JACK RUSSELL
TERRIERS SHE TRAINS AND BREEDS,

12:23.046 --> 12:26.180
SIMONE POSSESSES
STRONG HUNTING INSTINCTS

12:26.223 --> 12:30.662
THAT, IF LEFT UNCHECKED, COULD
RESULT IN DEADLY AGGRESSION.

12:30.706 --> 12:34.492
HAROLD HUNDIN'S FOURTH
AND FINAL WIFE WAS YOUNG HALLIE,

12:34.536 --> 12:35.885
WHO BRED LABRADORS

12:35.929 --> 12:39.323
AND DONATED THEM
AS SEEING EYE DOGS TO THE BLIND.

12:39.367 --> 12:42.370
LIKE HER LABS,
HALLIE WAS LOYAL, FRIENDLY,

12:42.413 --> 12:44.241
AND COMPETITIVELY OBEDIENT.

12:44.285 --> 12:47.592
SHE CRAVED HUMAN ATTENTION,
BUT IF DENIED,

12:47.636 --> 12:51.509
HER COMPETITIVE OBEDIENCE
COULD GO HORRIBLY AWRY.

12:56.776 --> 12:57.733
[ ENGINE STOPS ]

12:57.777 --> 12:59.343
Emerson: WAIT.

13:02.607 --> 13:04.305
WE GOING UNDERCOVER,

13:04.348 --> 13:06.611
AND BY "UNDERCOVER," I MEAN
THAT UNDER NO CIRCUMSTANCES

13:06.655 --> 13:09.876
ARE YOU TO REVEAL ANY FACTUAL
INFORMATION ABOUT YOUR PERSON.

13:09.919 --> 13:11.312
YOU MEAN YOU WANT US TO LIE.

13:11.355 --> 13:12.792
I WANT YOU TO LIE CONSISTENTLY,

13:12.835 --> 13:14.794
AND WE ALL GOT TO TAKE TURNS
WITH THE DOG.

13:14.837 --> 13:17.579
HE HAS A NAME, YOU KNOW.YEAH, AND YOU BETTER
LIE ABOUT THAT, TOO.

13:17.622 --> 13:20.887
[ BELL DINGS ]

13:20.930 --> 13:24.064
OH, YOU HAVE A GORGEOUS
SELECTION OF COUTURE.

13:24.107 --> 13:25.892
PICKLE LOVES HIM SOME D&G.

13:25.935 --> 13:28.416
[ BARKS ]HE'D LIKE TO KNOW
IF THAT COMES IN GREEN.

13:28.459 --> 13:31.506
I'M JUST KIDDING.
HE REALLY DIDN'T SAY THAT.

13:31.549 --> 13:33.421
HELLO, I'M PIMENTO.
AND YOU ARE?

13:33.464 --> 13:36.163
NED.
HAVE YOU HAD NED
SINCE HE WAS A PUPPY?

13:36.206 --> 13:38.556
NED AND I HAVE BEEN TOGETHER
FOR A VERY LONG TIME.

13:38.600 --> 13:40.167
WE'RE INTIMATE,

13:40.210 --> 13:42.604
BUT IT'S THE APPROPRIATE
HUMAN-CANINE SORT OF INTIMACY.

13:42.647 --> 13:44.867
HE DOESN'T RESPECT YOU.HE RESPECTS ME.

13:44.911 --> 13:47.000
TELL HIM TO SIT.
SIT.

13:49.437 --> 13:51.439
DAMN IT, DOG, YOU BETTER
SIT YOUR ASS DOWN.

13:51.482 --> 13:52.919
[ SNARLS ]

13:52.962 --> 13:55.225
[ CLEARS THROAT ]
HE DON'T WANT TO SIT.

13:55.269 --> 13:56.313
SIT.

13:56.357 --> 13:57.880
[ WHIMPERS ]

13:57.924 --> 14:02.189
YOU HAVE A VERY LOVELY HOME.
IT FEELS LOVELY.

14:02.232 --> 14:06.236
AND IT SMELLS LOVELY.
DO YOU USE AN AIR PURIFIER?

14:06.280 --> 14:07.716
IT HELPS WITH THE DANDER.

14:09.022 --> 14:10.327
HOW DID YOU LOSE YOUR SIGHT?

14:10.371 --> 14:11.981
I WAS CLEANING OUT
THE KITTY LITTER,

14:12.025 --> 14:13.504
AND I GOT CAT SAND
IN MY EYE.

14:13.548 --> 14:14.984
HORRIBLE INFECTION.
VERY SAD.

14:15.028 --> 14:16.290
I KNOW YOU'RE NOT BLIND.

14:16.333 --> 14:19.162
OH, THANK YOU.
I FELT AWFUL DOING THAT.

14:19.206 --> 14:20.729
IT WAS HUMILIATING
FOR BOTH OF US.

14:20.772 --> 14:24.472
HE LOOKS LIKE A PICKLE.
DOESN'T HE LOOK LIKE A PICKLE?

14:24.515 --> 14:26.909
DO YOU ALWAYS NAME
YOUR ANIMALS AFTER FOOD?

14:26.953 --> 14:29.607
MM-HMM. I USED TO HAVE A HORSE
NAMED THE PIE IN ANOTHER LIFE.

14:29.651 --> 14:31.871
THAT'S 'CAUSE I WANT TO BE
LIKE ELIZABETH TAYLOR.

14:31.914 --> 14:33.568
SHE WAS SO PRETTY.

14:33.611 --> 14:35.265
THEN THE PIE DIED.

14:35.309 --> 14:39.356
I JUST LOST MY DOG.
BUBBLEGUM.

14:39.400 --> 14:41.010
[ WHIMPERS ]

14:41.054 --> 14:44.318
I WAS IN SHOCK AFTER I LOST
MY PIE. THE HORSE, NOT THE FOOD.

14:44.361 --> 14:46.320
THEN ONE DAY
I WAS WALKING ALONG,

14:46.363 --> 14:49.062
AND I SAW A BAKERY
IN THE SHAPE OF A GIANT PIE.

14:49.105 --> 14:51.455
THE FOOD, NOT THE HORSE.

14:51.499 --> 14:52.892
IT WAS A SIGN.

14:52.935 --> 14:54.676
I DON'T KNOW WHAT IT SAID,
BUT IT WAS THERE.

14:54.719 --> 14:57.157
ARE YOU SUGGESTING THAT
I'LL FIND THE ANSWERS

14:57.200 --> 14:59.420
TO LIFE AND DEATH
IN A BUBBLEGUM MACHINE?

14:59.463 --> 15:00.856
BUBBLEGUM'S DEAD?

15:00.900 --> 15:02.249
I WAS LOOKING FORWARD
TO SURROUNDING HER

15:02.292 --> 15:03.815
IN WHITE LIGHT
AND POSITIVE ENERGY.

15:03.859 --> 15:05.339
I WASN'T QUITE SURE
HOW TO DO THAT,

15:05.382 --> 15:06.993
BUT I THOUGHT
AT LEAST I COULD DOG-SIT

15:07.036 --> 15:08.559
OR TAKE HER FOR A WALK
IN THE PARK.

15:08.603 --> 15:09.821
YOU KNEW ABOUT BUBBLEGUM?

15:09.865 --> 15:11.954
HAROLD LEFT A NOTE.

15:11.998 --> 15:13.738
WELL, SHE WAS EVERYTHING
TO HAROLD.

15:13.782 --> 15:15.044
WELL, WE ALL WERE.

15:15.088 --> 15:17.829
WE WERE FAMILY,
MY SISTER-WIVES AND ME.

15:17.873 --> 15:20.310
YOU DIDN'T MIND...

15:20.354 --> 15:22.051
SHARING?

15:22.095 --> 15:24.836
IT'S NOT AS IF
HE TREATED ME LIKE ONE
OF SO MANY BURIED BONES

15:24.880 --> 15:27.404
HE COULD DIG UP FROM THE YARD
WHENEVER HE SAW FIT?

15:27.448 --> 15:29.145
OH, I DIDN'T MEAN
TO SAY IT LIKE THAT.

15:29.189 --> 15:32.018
I WOULDN'T BE ALIVE
IF IT WEREN'T FOR HIM.LITERALLY?

15:32.061 --> 15:34.585
I WAS EXAGGERATING
FOR DRAMATIC EFFECT,

15:34.629 --> 15:37.632
BUT THAT'S THE WAY I FELT
WHEN WE WERE TOGETHER.

15:37.675 --> 15:41.418
AND IF YOU FEEL SOMETHING,
IT'S REAL.

15:41.462 --> 15:43.855
HOW DID BUBBLEGUM DIE?

15:43.899 --> 15:46.162
I BACKED UP OVER HER.DIDN'T LOOK
WHERE YOU WERE GOING?

15:46.206 --> 15:47.903
I JUST FOUND OUT MY HUSBAND
WAS MURDERED,

15:47.947 --> 15:49.861
AND IN MY PANIC TO GET
TO THE SCENE OF THE CRIME,

15:49.905 --> 15:51.428
I FORGOT TO CHECK
MY REARVIEW MIRROR.

15:51.472 --> 15:54.344
CLEARLY IT'S NOT
AN AFFECTIONATE RELATIONSHIP.

15:54.388 --> 15:57.739
OH, WE'RE VERY AFFECTIONATE.

15:57.782 --> 16:00.524
IT'S JUST...

16:00.568 --> 16:02.483
NED'S BEEN HAVING
STRANGE DREAMS LATELY.

16:02.526 --> 16:04.137
HIS PAWS TWITCH,
AND HE WHIMPERS.

16:04.180 --> 16:05.921
IT'D BE CUTE
IF IT WEREN'T SO SAD.

16:05.965 --> 16:09.098
HE MAY BE EXPERIENCING
STRESS-RELATED ANXIETY

16:09.142 --> 16:12.884
DUE TO, UH, MATING ISSUES.

16:12.928 --> 16:15.061
YOU'RE DEFLECTING.

16:15.104 --> 16:17.933
YOU'RE AVOIDING
A DEEPER DISCUSSION

16:17.977 --> 16:19.717
OF NED'S MATING ISSUES.

16:19.761 --> 16:21.763
CAN'T YOU SEE THIS IS MAKING NED
UNCOMFORTABLE?

16:21.806 --> 16:24.244
MR. DIGBY,
NED'S MERELY WRESTLING

16:24.287 --> 16:27.943
WITH THE NATURAL ANXIETIES
OF AN INEXPERIENCED STUD.

16:27.987 --> 16:30.380
HE'S HAD EXPERIENCE.
SOME.

16:31.860 --> 16:34.994
MATING ISN'T JUST FOR
THE BETTERMENT OF THE BREED.

16:35.037 --> 16:37.300
IT'S FOR THE BETTERMENT
OF THE DOG.

16:37.344 --> 16:40.956
PASSIONS THEY NEVER KNEW EVEN
EXISTED SUDDENLY BURST FORTH,

16:41.000 --> 16:44.481
ALLOWING DISCOVERY OF THEIR
TRUE PRIMAL SELVES AS THEY --

16:44.525 --> 16:47.267
Narrator: SHE WAS REFERRING
TO HER LATE HUSBAND, NOT DIGBY.

16:47.310 --> 16:49.356
EXCUSE ME.

16:51.880 --> 16:53.621
[ DOOR OPENS, CLOSES ]

16:53.664 --> 16:55.710
[ HEATHER SOBS ]

16:55.753 --> 16:58.887
Narrator:
HEATHER HUNDIN TOOK A MOMENT
TO MOURN HER HUSBAND, HAROLD,

16:58.930 --> 17:01.585
AND DIGBY AND THE PIE MAKER
TOOK A MOMENT

17:01.629 --> 17:04.197
TO POLITELY PRETEND
NOT TO NOTICE.

17:07.678 --> 17:09.463
WHERE WERE WE?

17:09.506 --> 17:11.639
HAROLD SPECIALIZED IN DESIGNER
BREEDS, LIKE THE JACK-A-POO.

17:11.682 --> 17:12.944
[ CLICKER CLICKS ]JACK-A-WHAT?

17:12.988 --> 17:14.381
THE JACK RUSSELL-POODLE MIX.

17:14.424 --> 17:16.209
THE COLL-A-DOR,
THE LAB-RUSSELL.

17:16.252 --> 17:18.515
IT WAS A NICHE,
BUT IT WAS HAROLD'S NICHE.

17:18.559 --> 17:20.169
Narrator:
AND THE APEX OF THAT NICHE

17:20.213 --> 17:23.129
WAS THE CREATION OF THE PERFECT
NEW BREED OF DOG

17:23.172 --> 17:26.784
HAROLD HUNDIN NAMED BUBBLEGUM.

17:26.828 --> 17:28.308
[ WHIMPERS ]

17:28.351 --> 17:30.527
SO, BUBBLEGUM WAS
A COLL-A-DOR-RUSSELL-A-POO.

17:30.571 --> 17:33.356
THE PERFECT HYBRID OF BORDER
COLLIE, LABRADOR RETRIEVER,

17:33.400 --> 17:35.184
JACK RUSSELL TERRIER,
AND POODLE.

17:35.228 --> 17:40.581
[ Voice breaking ] SMART, LOYAL,
ATHLETIC, AND...HYPOALLERGENIC.

17:40.624 --> 17:42.496
SHE'S WITH HAROLD NOW.

17:42.539 --> 17:45.281
SOUNDS LIKE YOU GAVE HAROLD
A LONG LEASH.

17:45.325 --> 17:47.501
I NEVER HELD HAROLD'S LEASH
OR HIS ANYTHING ELSE.

17:47.544 --> 17:49.981
HE WASN'T MY HOUND.
I WASN'T HIS BITCH.

17:50.025 --> 17:52.549
HE LIKED DOGS.
I LIKE DOGS.

17:52.593 --> 17:54.160
SO, NOTHING GOING ON
BETWEEN YOU TWO?

17:54.203 --> 17:56.510
WHAT WE HAD
WAS A TRAINED RESPONSE.

17:56.553 --> 17:58.512
HUMANS AND DOGS
ARE THE SAME.

17:58.555 --> 18:00.731
SUPPLY THE RIGHT CUE...

18:00.775 --> 18:04.083
[ CLICKER CLICKS ]...AND THEY RESPOND
ACCORDINGLY.

18:04.126 --> 18:07.216
THE ONLY CUE WE EVER GAVE
EACH OTHER WAS COMMERCIAL.

18:07.260 --> 18:09.436
SO, YOU TWO
JUST USED EACH OTHER.

18:09.479 --> 18:11.699
HAVEN'T YOU EVER USED SOMEONE
FOR COMMERCIAL GAIN?

18:11.742 --> 18:14.005
[ CHUCKLES ]

18:14.049 --> 18:16.399
WHEN WAS THE LAST TIME
YOU SAW HAROLD ALIVE?

18:16.443 --> 18:18.009
RIGHT BEFORE HE DIED.

18:18.053 --> 18:20.751
I HANDED HIM HIS COFFEE,
AND I KISSED HIM GOODBYE.

18:20.795 --> 18:22.188
THE MORNING HE DIED.

18:22.231 --> 18:23.754
I GAVE HIM HIS COFFEE.

18:23.798 --> 18:26.235
I GAVE HIM
HIS MORNING COFFEE,

18:26.279 --> 18:28.933
AND IT WAS THE LAST
I SAW OF HIM.

18:28.977 --> 18:31.240
I SAID, "WHY DON'T YOU COME
BY FOR SOME COFFEE?"

18:31.284 --> 18:32.894
WE HAD SOME THINGS
TO DISCUSS.

18:32.937 --> 18:35.418
SO HE CAME BY.
WE DISCUSSED THOSE THINGS.

18:35.462 --> 18:38.508
HE TOOK HIS COFFEE TO GO,
AND THEN HE DIED.

18:38.552 --> 18:41.076
MY WIFE DID IT.
SHE HAD MURDER IN HER EYES.

18:41.120 --> 18:42.773
AND THAT MURDER WAS COUTURE.

18:42.817 --> 18:45.950
MY WIFE GAVE HIM
HIS MORNING COFFEE.All: SO DID MINE.

18:45.994 --> 18:48.127
NO WONDER THE GUY CAN
HANDLE FOUR WIVES.
THE DUDE'S CAFFEINATED.

18:48.170 --> 18:50.477
I DON'T THINK HALLIE
DID IT. SHE DIDN'T GIVE
ME THAT IMPRESSION.

18:50.520 --> 18:52.783
DID SHE GIVE HIM
SOME MORNING COFFEE?SHE SAID SHE GAVE HIM
HIS MORNING COFFEE,

18:52.827 --> 18:54.437
KISSED HIM GOODBYE, WHICH
IS PRACTICALLY A CONFESSION,

18:54.481 --> 18:55.699
BUT I STILL
DON'T THINK SHE DID IT.

18:55.743 --> 18:57.266
Olive: THERE SHE IS NOW.
YOU CAN ASK HER.

18:57.310 --> 18:59.355
[ DOOR OPENS, BELLS RING ]

18:59.399 --> 19:01.227
THAT'S HER.
THE LITTLE ONE.

19:01.270 --> 19:02.445
MR. DIGBY.

19:02.489 --> 19:03.925
HI, HALLIE!
HI, CHUCK.

19:03.968 --> 19:05.753
SIT.[ CLICKER CLICKS ]

19:05.796 --> 19:07.276
HOW DID YOU GUYS
FIND US?

19:07.320 --> 19:09.452
JUST LOOKED FOR THE BAKERY
SHAPED LIKE A GIANT PIE.

19:09.496 --> 19:11.672
THE FOOD, NOT THE HORSE.

19:11.715 --> 19:13.891
WE UNDERSTAND
HAROLD LEFT A NOTE.WHO SAID ANYTHING
ABOUT A NOTE?

19:13.935 --> 19:15.371
I SAID ABOUT THE NOTE.

19:17.373 --> 19:19.201
"UNDER," MEANING "BELOW."

19:19.245 --> 19:21.334
"COVER," MEANING
"THE RADAR," PEOPLE.

19:21.377 --> 19:23.727
WHAT IS SO HARD ABOUT THAT
TO UNDERSTAND?

19:23.771 --> 19:25.773
SORRY.
WHO ARE YOU PEOPLE?

19:25.816 --> 19:27.209
WE'LL GET TO THE PARTICULARS
OF THAT

19:27.253 --> 19:28.993
ONCE YOU GET
TO THE PARTICULARS OF THIS.

19:29.037 --> 19:30.821
WHAT KIND OF CREAM DID YOU PUT
IN HAROLD'S COFFEE?
SOY.

19:30.865 --> 19:33.737
HEAVY CREAM.I DON'T PUT CREAM
IN MY COFFEE.

19:33.781 --> 19:38.002
I USE ALMOND-FLAVORED
COFFEE CREAM CREAMER.

19:38.046 --> 19:39.526
[ GASPS ]

19:46.097 --> 19:47.838
THE POLICE WRESTLED LITTLE
HALLIE HUNDIN TO THE GROUND.

19:47.882 --> 19:49.797
TO THE GROUND,
AND SHE'S SMALL.

19:49.840 --> 19:52.408
IT WAS LIKE A LION
TAKING DOWN A BABY ZEBRA.

19:52.452 --> 19:55.237
WE WERE AWFUL TOURISTS SITTING
SAFELY IN OUR CAMOUFLAGED S.U.V.

19:55.281 --> 19:56.891
WATCHING THE INJUSTICE.

19:56.934 --> 19:59.850
"INJUSTICE"?
THEY FOUND CYANIDE
IN HER COFFEE.

19:59.894 --> 20:01.896
MY WIFE, THE BABY ZEBRA,
IS OBVIOUSLY BEING SET UP.

20:01.939 --> 20:03.680
SHE BREEDS HELPER PUPPIES
FOR BLIND CHILDREN.

20:03.724 --> 20:05.247
I MEAN, SHE'S NO KILLER.

20:05.291 --> 20:06.944
SHE'S AN ANGEL.

20:06.988 --> 20:08.381
YEAH, ANGEL OF DEATH.

20:08.424 --> 20:10.644
KENNEL CLUB DIDN'T THINK
BABY ZEBRA WAS SET UP,

20:10.687 --> 20:12.123
AND NEITHER DID THE POLICE.

20:12.167 --> 20:13.995
HALLIE DID LOOK INNOCENT.

20:14.038 --> 20:15.692
I KNOW THAT SOUNDS SILLY COMING
FROM A PRIVATE INVESTIGATOR --

20:15.736 --> 20:17.085
YES, IT DOES.

20:17.128 --> 20:19.261
BUT AS A BAKER OF PIES,
IT'S NOT SILLY AT ALL.

20:19.305 --> 20:20.697
I LOOK AT A PIE BAKING,

20:20.741 --> 20:22.830
I KNOW IF IT'S DONE
OR IF IT'S NOT DONE.

20:22.873 --> 20:25.441
I CAN'T TELL YOU HOW I KNOW
OR WHY, BUT I KNOW.

20:25.485 --> 20:27.748
IT'S TRUTH FROM THAT DARK,
DEEP-ROOTED PLACE

20:27.791 --> 20:28.966
DEEP DOWN INSIDE.

20:29.010 --> 20:31.273
[ TELEPHONE RINGS ]

20:31.317 --> 20:33.971
PIE HOLE.

20:34.015 --> 20:35.538
IT'S...FOR YOU.

20:36.409 --> 20:39.542
Narrator: AS THE PIE MAKER
CONSIDERED ALL OF THE TRUTHS

20:39.586 --> 20:42.676
HE WAS KEEPING BURIED
WITHIN HIS DEEP-ROOTED PLACE

20:42.719 --> 20:44.721
AND FAR AWAY FROM CHUCK...

20:44.765 --> 20:47.289
YES, WE DO.
I CERTAINLY CAN.

20:47.333 --> 20:49.422
[ CHUCKLES ]
BYE, NOW.

20:49.465 --> 20:54.078
Narrator:
...EMERSON COD CONSIDERED 25,000
NEW REASONS TO REOPEN THE CASE.

20:54.122 --> 20:56.298
UH, WE NEED TO PROVE
HALLIE HUNDIN WAS INNOCENT.

20:56.342 --> 20:58.082
YOUR CONSCIENCE CALLS YOU
ON THE TELEPHONE?

20:58.126 --> 21:00.520
THOSE BLIND KIDS THAT HALLIE
GAVE HER PUPPIES TO

21:00.563 --> 21:02.609
HAVE PUT TOGETHER
A "FREE HALLIE" FUND.

21:02.652 --> 21:04.785
WE EXONERATE HALLIE,
WE COLLECT A REWARD.

21:04.828 --> 21:07.570
[ GROANS ]YOU'RE TAKING MONEY
FROM BLIND CHILDREN?

21:07.614 --> 21:10.356
I SUPPOSE I COULD PAY MY BILLS
WITH BLIND KIDS' SMILES,

21:10.399 --> 21:12.488
BUT THEIR MONEY
IS A LOT EASIER.

21:12.532 --> 21:13.533
[ NEWSPAPER SNAPS ]

21:13.576 --> 21:15.317
EVERYBODY'S BEEN REALLY NICE.

21:15.361 --> 21:18.625
IT'S NOT AT ALL LIKE THOSE
PRISON-EXPLOITATION FILMS.

21:18.668 --> 21:20.322
SO, YOU DON'T NEED
CIGARETTES OR ALCOHOL

21:20.366 --> 21:22.193
OR THE RIGHT MOISTURIZER
TO USE AS CURRENCY?

21:22.237 --> 21:24.413
OH, NO.
THAT'S MY FRIEND TERESA.

21:24.457 --> 21:28.156
SHE SAYS SHE RUNS THE CELLBLOCK,
SO I'M PROTECTED.

21:28.199 --> 21:30.027
SHE SLEEPS A LOT FOR SOMEONE
WHO RUNS A CELLBLOCK.

21:30.071 --> 21:31.855
I DON'T THINK IT'S BEEN
AN EASY ROAD FOR HER.

21:31.899 --> 21:33.422
WELL, IT'LL BE
A LOT EASIER ROAD FOR YOU

21:33.466 --> 21:35.163
ONCE YOU HELP US FIND OUT
WHO KILLED HAROLD.

21:35.206 --> 21:37.513
HALLIE, WAS IT HILARY,
HEATHER, OR SIMONE?

21:37.557 --> 21:40.037
IT COULDN'T HAVE BEEN
ANY OF MY SISTER-WIVES.

21:40.081 --> 21:42.301
WE ALL LOVED HAROLD TOO MUCH
TO KILL HIM.

21:42.344 --> 21:44.651
OH, NO, IT WAS ONE OF YOUR
SISTER-WIVES. HAROLD SAID SO.

21:45.565 --> 21:48.132
IN HIS NOTE.

21:48.176 --> 21:50.221
IF YOU ASK ME --
OH, ARE YOU ASKING ME?

21:50.265 --> 21:51.222
YES.

21:51.266 --> 21:53.050
IT WAS RAMSFELD SNUPPY.

21:53.094 --> 21:55.270
HE'S ANOTHER NICHE DOG BREEDER,
BUT NOT AS NICHE AS HAROLD.

21:55.314 --> 21:56.663
SNUPPY WANTED OUR BUBBLEGUM.

21:56.706 --> 21:58.491
SNUPPY WANTED
TO COLLABORATE WITH HAROLD

21:58.534 --> 22:00.493
TO MAKE COLL-A-DOR-RUSSELL-A-POO
SUPERPUPPIES,

22:00.536 --> 22:03.104
BUT I THINK SNUPPY WANTED
ALL THE DOGGY TREATS TO HIMSELF.

22:03.147 --> 22:05.019
HE COULD HAVE EASILY
PLANTED THE CYANIDE

22:05.062 --> 22:07.021
IN MY ALMOND-FLAVORED COFFEE
CREAM CREAMER.

22:07.064 --> 22:09.153
BUT MURDER
FOR A FEW PUPPIES?

22:09.197 --> 22:11.068
SNUPPY HAD BIG PLANS FOR HER.

22:11.112 --> 22:12.766
Narrator:
THE FACTS WERE THESE --

22:12.809 --> 22:16.378
ONE RAMSFELD SNUPPY WAS THE SON
OF A FURNITURE LIQUIDATOR

22:16.422 --> 22:18.467
AND SHOPPING NETWORK HAND MODEL.

22:18.511 --> 22:19.903
WOOF WOOF WOOF.

22:19.947 --> 22:22.558
HOW MUCH IS THAT PUPPY
IN THE WINDOW?

22:22.602 --> 22:26.257
WELL, SHE CAN BE YOURS
FOR 12 EASY PAYMENTS OF $129.95.

22:26.301 --> 22:28.912
Narrator: AND HE WENT FROM
A SINGLE STOREFRONT PUPPY SHOP

22:28.956 --> 22:30.566
IN FROGNOT, TEXAS,

22:30.610 --> 22:34.701
TO A NATIONWIDE EMPIRE OF
SNUPPY'S PUPPIES CHAIN STORES.

22:34.744 --> 22:38.357
FOR RAMSFELD SNUPPY,
MONEY DIDN'T GROW ON TREES.

22:38.400 --> 22:40.446
IT WAS MADE IN CAGES.

22:40.489 --> 22:43.579
I WAS LISTENING TO
HEATHER HUNDIN'S WEEKLY
RADIO SHOW, "DOGGONIT,"

22:43.623 --> 22:46.626
AND SHE SAID THAT
DOG BREEDING'S A LOT
HARDER THAN YOU THINK.

22:46.669 --> 22:48.410
IT LOOKS EASY ENOUGH.NO, IT'S NOT.

22:48.454 --> 22:50.194
THERE'S ALL THESE HOOPS
THE PROSPECTIVE MATES

22:50.238 --> 22:52.109
HAVE TO JUMP THROUGH
TO SEE IF THEY'RE COMPATIBLE.

22:52.153 --> 22:53.676
LIKE THEIR SMELL
AND THEIR TASTES.

22:53.720 --> 22:55.896
THEY EVEN HAVE THEIR OWN
KIND OF DOGGY KISSING.

22:55.939 --> 22:57.593
A BIT LIKE PEOPLE KISSING.

22:57.637 --> 22:59.769
I thought you said
you wasn't gonna tell her.

22:59.813 --> 23:01.162
I didn't.

23:01.205 --> 23:02.946
YOU DIDN'T HAVE TO.
OLIVE ALREADY DID.

23:02.990 --> 23:05.296
BUT FOR THE RECORD, I'D HAVE
PREFERRED TO HEAR IT FROM YOU.

23:05.340 --> 23:07.342
THE ONLY REASON
I DIDN'T TELL YOU WAS
BECAUSE IT DIDN'T MATTER.

23:07.386 --> 23:09.953
LOTS OF STUFF GOES ON IN
THE COURSE OF A DAY THAT
I DON'T BOTHER SHARING.

23:09.997 --> 23:12.478
FOR INSTANCE,
YESTERDAY'S 4-BERRY PIE
WAS ACTUALLY 3 1/2

23:12.521 --> 23:15.568
BECAUSE I RAN OUT
OF CRANBERRIES.

23:15.611 --> 23:17.787
I DIDN'T TELL YOU THAT.ACTUALLY, YOU DID.

23:17.831 --> 23:19.441
YOU ASKED IF ORANGE
COUNTED AS A BERRY,

23:19.485 --> 23:21.487
AND I SAID IT DIDN'T,
BUT NO ONE HAD TO KNOW BUT US.

23:21.530 --> 23:22.792
I LIKE THAT YOU SAID "US."

23:22.836 --> 23:24.838
WELL, WE ARE AN "US,"
AREN'T WE?

23:24.881 --> 23:26.927
WE'RE JUST AN "US"
WITH SPECIAL CIRCUMSTANCES.

23:28.450 --> 23:30.539
WHY DO I ALWAYS HAVE TO BE
AROUND FOR THIS STUFF?

23:30.583 --> 23:33.281
MAYBE WE JUST HAVE TO EMBRACE
THE IDEA THAT SOMETIMES --

23:33.324 --> 23:35.239
SOMETIMES I MIGHT HAVE TO
HOLD SOMEONE ELSE'S HANDS

23:35.283 --> 23:37.328
AND SOMETIMES YOU MIGHT HAVE
TO KISS SOMEBODY ELSE'S --

23:37.372 --> 23:39.461
I DON'T WANT TO KISS
ANYONE ELSE'S ANYTHING.

23:39.505 --> 23:42.638
BUT MAYBE THERE'S SOMETHING TO
THIS POLYGAMY THING, YOU KNOW?

23:42.682 --> 23:44.423
MAYBE ONE PERSON
ISN'T ENOUGH.

23:44.466 --> 23:46.163
WHAT?

23:46.207 --> 23:47.730
Ramsfeld: HOWDY, FOLKS.

23:47.774 --> 23:48.992
Chuck: HI.

23:49.036 --> 23:51.342
WHAT CAN I DO FOR YOU?

23:51.386 --> 23:53.040
WE HEAR
YOU'RE THE MAN TO SEE

23:53.083 --> 23:54.650
IF WE WANT TO GET OUR HANDS ON
A COLL-A-DOR-RUSSELL-A-POO.

23:54.694 --> 23:55.999
THERE'S A WAITING LIST,
THOUGH.

23:56.043 --> 23:57.436
WE'RE A LITTLE BEHIND
ON MANUFACTURING.

23:57.479 --> 23:59.089
MANUFACTURING?

23:59.133 --> 24:01.440
YEAH, WE HAD A LITTLE
REPRODUCTIVE SETBACK

24:01.483 --> 24:03.311
WHEN THE ALPHA DOG
GOT RUN OVER.

24:03.354 --> 24:05.966
BUT THAT DOESN'T MEAN
THERE WON'T BE A SUPERHYBRID PUP

24:06.009 --> 24:07.924
UNDER EVERY CHRISTMAS TREE
THIS YEAR.

24:07.968 --> 24:10.971
HOW DO YOU PLAN TO BREED A
BUBBLE THAT'S BURST OR RUN OVER,

24:11.014 --> 24:12.494
AS THE CASE MAY BE?

24:12.538 --> 24:14.409
SON, WHY GO THROUGH
ALL THE HASSLE OF BREEDING

24:14.453 --> 24:17.107
WHEN WE CAN CREATE THE PERFECT
COPY OF MAN'S BEST BEST FRIEND

24:17.151 --> 24:21.285
EVERY TIME AVAILABLE EXCLUSIVELY
AT A SNUPPY'S PUPPIES NEAR YOU?

24:21.329 --> 24:25.289
I'M GONNA CLONE BUBBLEGUM
FROM HER REMAINS.

24:25.333 --> 24:27.378
ALL I GOT TO DO
IS FIND SOME VIABLE DNAs,

24:27.422 --> 24:29.511
FUSE THEM INTO
SOME DENUCLEATED EGG CELLS,

24:29.555 --> 24:31.382
AND PLANT THE EGGS
IN SURROGATE DOGS

24:31.426 --> 24:33.776
IN ALL MY NATIONWIDE STORES,
AND WOOF WOOF WOOF --

24:33.820 --> 24:36.300
MORE LITTERS OF IDENTICAL
COLL-A-DOR-RUSSELL-A-POOS

24:36.344 --> 24:37.606
THAN YOU CAN COUNT.

24:37.650 --> 24:39.347
BUT BUBBLEGUM
WASN'T YOUR DOG!

24:41.480 --> 24:43.177
WELL, SHE WASN'T.

24:46.441 --> 24:49.357
ARE YOU THE HUNDIN LAWYERS?WE'RE FRIENDS
OF THE HUNDIN LAWYERS.

24:49.400 --> 24:53.100
THEY SAW THE CONTRACT.
THEY KNOW THE WHOLE DEAL.

24:53.143 --> 24:56.712
I OWN BUBBLEGUM
DEAD OR ALIVE.HAROLD SOLD YOU BUBBLEGUM?

24:56.756 --> 24:59.323
AGAINST HIS WIVES'
WISHES. PROBABLY WHY
THEY WANTED HIM DEAD.

24:59.367 --> 25:02.239
BUT THE INK WAS DRY
BEFORE HALLIE GOT TO HIM.

25:02.283 --> 25:04.546
I GOT WHAT WAS COMING TO ME.

25:04.590 --> 25:06.330
SOMEONE I NEED TO SEE.

25:06.374 --> 25:08.507
[ CLICKER CLICKS ]

25:08.550 --> 25:10.857
Emerson:
YOU KNEW HAROLD WAS GONNA
SELL BUBBLEGUM TO SNUPPY,

25:10.900 --> 25:13.555
YET YOU NEGLECTED TO MENTION
IT IN OUR PREVIOUS CONVERSATION.

25:13.599 --> 25:16.863
AND YOU THINK THAT
GAVE ME ENOUGH MOTIVE
TO KILL MY HUSBAND?

25:16.906 --> 25:18.473
THAT'S EXACTLY
WHAT I THINK.

25:18.517 --> 25:20.519
YOU THINK WRONG.
I DIDN'T KILL HAROLD.

25:20.562 --> 25:21.955
HALLIE THINKS SNUPPY DID IT.

25:21.998 --> 25:23.826
HALLIE WOULD FETCH A BALL
IN TRAFFIC IF ASKED,

25:23.870 --> 25:26.699
BUT IN THIS CASE,
SHE ISN'T NECESSARILY WRONG.KEEP TALKING.

25:26.742 --> 25:28.744
WHEN HAROLD CAME TO US
WITH HIS PLAN, WE THREATENED

25:28.788 --> 25:30.746
TO GET AN INJUNCTION
AS PARTNERS IN THE BUSINESS.

25:30.790 --> 25:33.227
THAT WOULD HAVE HELD UP
SNUPPY'S PLANS FOR YEARS,

25:33.270 --> 25:36.186
SO HE KILLED HAROLD
AND FRAMED HALLIE.THAT'S ONE THEORY.

25:36.230 --> 25:38.928
ANOTHER ONE IS WHEN YOU HEARD
ABOUT HAROLD AND HIS PLAN,

25:38.972 --> 25:41.452
YOU PUT AN INJUNCTION
IN THE BLOOD FLOW TO HIS HEART.

25:41.496 --> 25:44.238
DO I SEEM CAPABLE
OF THAT KIND OF AGGRESSION?

25:44.281 --> 25:46.370
WELL, YOU NEVER KNOW
WHAT THE BODY'S CAPABLE OF

25:46.414 --> 25:48.982
UNTIL YOU MESS
WITH THEIR KIBBLE.

25:49.025 --> 25:50.200
SO DON'T MESS.

25:50.244 --> 25:52.899
[ CLICKER CLICKS ]

25:58.469 --> 26:00.994
Narrator: IF HE HAD
PAID ATTENTION WHILE AWAKE,

26:01.037 --> 26:02.822
EMERSON COD
WOULD HAVE FOUND THE EVIDENCE

26:02.865 --> 26:05.607
POINTING TOWARD
SIMONE HUNDIN'S GUILT.

26:12.658 --> 26:15.486
FEELING SOMETHING WAS AMISS
AT THE K-18 DOG STUDIO,

26:15.530 --> 26:18.794
EMERSON COD'S SUBCONSCIOUS MIND
PUT IT TOGETHER

26:18.838 --> 26:20.970
BEFORE HIS CONSCIOUS MIND COULD.

26:21.014 --> 26:25.322
SOMEONE OR SOME DOG
WAS USING BUBBLEGUM'S COLLAR.

26:25.366 --> 26:30.632
EMERSON COD'S DREAMS HAD GIFTED
HIM THE COLLAR AS A CLUE.

26:34.070 --> 26:36.507
HE KNEW BUBBLEGUM WAS ALIVE

26:36.551 --> 26:40.860
AND THAT HAROLD HUNDIN'S KILLER
WAS INDEED STILL ON THE LOOSE.

26:40.903 --> 26:45.734
BUT WORSE, HE FEARED
HE WAS FALLING FOR HER.

27:00.531 --> 27:03.317
THAT DOG IS ALIVE.ALIVE OR ALIVE AGAIN?

27:03.360 --> 27:06.407
THE NEVER-BEEN-DEAD
KIND OF ALIVE.AND YOU GOT ALL THIS
FROM A DREAM?

27:06.450 --> 27:08.235
I THOUGHT DREAMS WERE JUST
SUPPOSED TO BE YOUR BRAIN

27:08.278 --> 27:09.976
TRYING TO PROCESS
RANDOM RIGMAROLE IT
COULDN'T FIND A PLACE FOR.

27:10.019 --> 27:12.587
SOMETIMES IN THAT RANDOM
RIGMAROLE, THERE'S A CLUE.

27:12.631 --> 27:15.198
I'M GONNA SHAKE DOWN SIMONE.
I'M GONNA FIND THAT DOG.

27:15.242 --> 27:17.679
IF YOU SHAKE SIMONE
AND THE DOG FALLS OUT --

27:17.723 --> 27:20.247
THEN SHE'S THE KILLER.

27:20.290 --> 27:24.120
Narrator:
FEARING BEING ALONE WITH THE
GIRL HE KISSED BUT DID NOT LOVE

27:24.164 --> 27:26.688
AND THE GIRL HE LOVED
BUT COULD NOT KISS,

27:26.732 --> 27:28.603
THE PIE MAKER DECIDED...

27:28.647 --> 27:31.345
I'LL COME WITH YOU.THIS IS A SOLO SHAKING.

27:33.913 --> 27:36.350
[ DOOR OPENS, BELLS RING ]

27:36.393 --> 27:38.744
HI.
HELLO. OLIVE.

27:38.787 --> 27:40.441
LOOK, I KNOW THINGS HAVE GOTTEN
A SMIDGE AWKWARD

27:40.484 --> 27:42.095
SINCE THE WHOLE --AWKWARD? THIS ISN'T AWKWARD.

27:42.138 --> 27:43.705
IT WAS JUST A KISS,
AND I DON'T EVEN THINK

27:43.749 --> 27:45.620
OUR SALIVA WAS COMPATIBLE,
SO THERE'S NO REASON TO DISCUSS

27:45.664 --> 27:48.841
AND MAKE SOMETHING THAT
ISN'T AWKWARD...AWKWARD.

27:54.107 --> 27:56.196
Narrator:
OLIVE PONDERED THE BLACK MARK

27:56.239 --> 27:58.328
ON HER RELATIONSHIP
WITH THE PIE MAKER

27:58.372 --> 28:00.722
SHE FEARED WAS INKED
WITH A PERMANENT MARKER.

28:00.766 --> 28:03.899
I REALLY SCREWED THE POOCH,
DIDN'T I?

28:04.683 --> 28:06.467
[ BELLS RING ]

28:06.989 --> 28:08.774
YOUR ORDER FOR PICKLE
CAME IN.

28:08.817 --> 28:11.298
THAT ORDER WAS PLACED
UNDER FALSE PRETENSES.

28:11.341 --> 28:13.300
FORTUNATELY YOUR CREDIT CARD
WAS REAL.

28:13.343 --> 28:15.128
WELL, HAPPY BIRTHDAY TO DIGBY

28:15.171 --> 28:17.957
AND CONGRATULATIONS TO YOU,
TOO, I SUPPOSE.

28:18.000 --> 28:20.786
FOR WHAT?I HEARD ABOUT THE PLANS
FOR CLONING BUBBLEGUM.

28:20.829 --> 28:23.310
GUESS YOU'LL BE GETTING YOUR
BABY BACK AFTER ALL, IN A WAY.

28:23.353 --> 28:25.225
SNUPPY CAN CLONE BUBBLEGUM?

28:25.268 --> 28:27.880
IT HAS TO DO WITH DNA
AND NUCLEUSES.

28:27.923 --> 28:31.274
WELL, I WAS NEVER VERY GOOD
AT SCIENCE, BUT YAY.

28:31.318 --> 28:32.623
YAY!

28:32.667 --> 28:35.235
Narrator:
AT THE K-18 OBEDIENCE CENTER,

28:35.278 --> 28:38.673
EMERSON COD BELIEVED
HE HAD FOUND THE REAL KILLER.

28:38.717 --> 28:40.501
Emerson: WHY IS IT THAT
BUBBLEGUM'S COLLAR MOVES AROUND

28:40.544 --> 28:41.763
EVERY TIME I COME OVER HERE?

28:41.807 --> 28:43.722
I'M THINKING IT'S BECAUSE

28:43.765 --> 28:46.812
YOU CAN'T WALK A DOG
WITHOUT A COLLAR.

28:46.855 --> 28:48.509
AND GUESS WHAT ELSE.

28:48.552 --> 28:50.467
YOU CAN'T WALK A DEAD DOG.

28:50.511 --> 28:54.689
SO I'M ONLY GONNA ASK YOU THIS
ONCE. WHERE'S BUBBLEGUM?

28:54.733 --> 28:56.430
YOU'VE GOT ME.

28:56.473 --> 28:58.693
I'VE GOT HER, AND I KNEW
IF YOU KNEW I HAD HER,

28:58.737 --> 29:00.651
YOU'D ASSUME I KILLED HAROLD
TO KEEP HER.

29:00.695 --> 29:03.350
YEAH, QUICKLY ADDING UP
TO BE A LITTLE MORE
THAN JUST AN ASSUMPTION.

29:03.393 --> 29:05.744
I CAN ONLY SAY I DIDN'T KILL
MY HUSBAND SO MANY TIMES,

29:05.787 --> 29:07.833
BUT FOR GOOD MEASURE,
I DIDN'T KILL MY HUSBAND.

29:07.876 --> 29:09.530
YOU CAN SAY IT ALL YOU WANT.
I STOPPED LISTENING.

29:09.573 --> 29:11.053
THE ONLY THING I WANT TO HEAR

29:11.097 --> 29:13.316
IS THE CLICKETY-CLACK OF
BUBBLEGUM'S PAWS ON THE FLOOR

29:13.360 --> 29:15.101
AS YOU BRING EXHIBIT "A"
ON OUT HERE.

29:15.144 --> 29:17.494
YOU SEEM MORE CONCERNED
ABOUT BUBBLEGUM

29:17.538 --> 29:19.932
THAN WHO KILLED HAROLD.

29:23.239 --> 29:26.199
STOP PLAYING AND GO SHOW ME
THAT SUPERDOG.

29:28.244 --> 29:29.811
IT'S TIME
FOR HER WALK ANYWAY.

29:29.855 --> 29:31.465
I'LL GO AND FETCH MY COAT.

29:31.508 --> 29:33.815
GRAB HER COLLAR
FROM THE PEDESTAL THERE.
OKAY.

29:33.859 --> 29:36.818
Narrator: SIMONE HUNDIN HAD BEEN
SUBCONSCIOUSLY TRAINING

29:36.862 --> 29:42.302
EMERSON COD, WHO HAD A STRONG
DESIRE TO DO AS SHE COMMANDED.

29:42.345 --> 29:44.217
[ MUFFLED SHOUTING ]

30:05.891 --> 30:07.806
[ BUBBLEGUM GROWLING ]

30:09.633 --> 30:11.070
[ MUFFLED TALKING ]

30:11.113 --> 30:13.463
Simone:
BUBBLEGUM, HEEL.

30:16.902 --> 30:19.382
THIS WILL GO A LOT EASIER
IF YOU COOPERATE.

30:19.426 --> 30:21.210
OW!
[ TOY SQUEAKS ]

30:21.254 --> 30:22.733
WHO THE HELL
YOU THINK YOU PLAYING?

30:22.777 --> 30:24.692
I'M ASKING THE QUESTIONS.

30:24.735 --> 30:27.173
HOW LONG HAVE YOU BEEN WORKING
FOR SNUPPY?I DON'T WORK FOR SNUPPY.

30:27.216 --> 30:29.088
A BUNCH OF BLIND KIDS
WITH TOO MUCH MONEY

30:29.131 --> 30:32.265
PAID ME TO EXONERATE
YOUR SISTER-WIFE HALLIE.I DON'T BELIEVE YOU.

30:32.308 --> 30:35.790
I THINK HE HIRED YOU TO SEE
IF I FAKED BUBBLEGUM'S DEATH.WELL, WHY WOULD HE DO THAT?

30:35.834 --> 30:38.010
'CAUSE HE CAN'T CLONE
A DEAD DOG.
YEAH, HE CAN.

30:38.053 --> 30:39.925
YOU GAVE HIM
EVERYTHING HE NEEDED

30:39.968 --> 30:42.101
WHEN YOU HANDED HIM
BUBBLEGUM'S ASHES.

30:42.144 --> 30:44.712
ONLY THEY WEREN'T BUBBLEGUM'S
ASHES, WERE THEY?

30:44.755 --> 30:47.280
BUBBLEGUM, GO HIDE.

30:47.323 --> 30:49.630
IF YOU'LL EXCUSE ME, I HAVE
SOME LEFTOVER BUSINESS TO HANDLE

30:49.673 --> 30:52.459
AND A FUNERAL TO ATTEND.AS LONG AS IT AIN'T MINE,
I'M COOL.

30:52.502 --> 30:54.287
THAT REMAINS TO BE SEEN.

31:05.515 --> 31:06.952
Narrator:
EMERSON COD'S HATRED OF THE DARK

31:06.995 --> 31:08.823
BEGAN AFTER A CHILDHOOD PRANK

31:08.867 --> 31:12.261
IN WHICH HE WAS LOCKED IN A
WASHING MACHINE FOR TWO NIGHTS.

31:12.305 --> 31:14.307
FINDING HIMSELF
SIMILARLY TRAPPED,

31:14.350 --> 31:17.179
HIS ADRENALINE LEVEL SKYROCKETED
TO A HEIGHT

31:17.223 --> 31:21.444
IN WHICH NEAR SUPERHUMAN
STRENGTH WAS ACHIEVED.

31:23.664 --> 31:24.970
AH! YEAH! UH-OH!

31:25.013 --> 31:26.449
[ THUD ]

31:26.493 --> 31:28.103
YEAH, THAT'S GONNA BRUISE.

31:28.712 --> 31:30.584
HEY!

31:30.627 --> 31:33.195
MY WIFE IS GONNA KILL RAMSFELD
SNUPPY. SHE'S NOT MYWIFE.

31:33.239 --> 31:35.719
SIMONE, THE WIFE AT -- YOU KNOW
WHAT THE HELL I'M SAYING.

31:35.763 --> 31:36.764
COME ON!

31:42.857 --> 31:44.990
DON'T THINK
IT'S ALMOND LATTE.

31:45.033 --> 31:46.774
OH, YOU THINK
IT MIGHT BE CYANIDE?

31:46.817 --> 31:49.124
WHY CAN'T IT EVER BE
SIMPLE, EASY?

31:49.168 --> 31:50.517
HE SAYS, "MY WIFE."

31:50.560 --> 31:52.867
HOW HARD
COULD THAT POSSIBLY BE?

31:52.911 --> 31:54.825
HALLIE DIDN'T DO IT.
SHE'S BEHIND BARS.

31:54.869 --> 31:56.479
IT MUST HAVE BEEN SIMONE.

31:56.523 --> 31:57.872
IT MIGHT NOT BE SIMONE.

31:57.916 --> 31:59.613
SIMONE WAS HIDING BUBBLEGUM.

31:59.656 --> 32:02.007
SHE CHLOROFORMED YOU
AND TIED YOU UP.

32:02.050 --> 32:04.661
I'M NOT EVEN GONNA MENTION
THE BALL GAG.

32:04.705 --> 32:06.707
THAT'S GANGSTER LOVE.

32:06.750 --> 32:08.709
SEE?
THAT'S WHAT'S RUBBING ME.

32:08.752 --> 32:11.451
IF SHE WAS GANGSTER, SHE'D HAVE
BUSTED A CYANIDE CAP IN MY ASS

32:11.494 --> 32:13.714
THE MINUTE I SNIFFED OUT
HER DOG, BUT SHE DIDN'T.

32:13.757 --> 32:16.064
WHY DON'T
WE JUST ASK HIM?[ SIGHS ]

32:20.547 --> 32:22.027
WAIT, WAIT, WAIT! STOP.

32:22.070 --> 32:24.768
WE'RE ABOUT TO TAKE ANOTHER TRIP
DOWN POINTLESS CREEK.

32:24.812 --> 32:27.293
OKAY, MAYBE SIMONE DID IT.
MAYBE SHE DIDN'T.

32:27.336 --> 32:30.296
BUT HAROLD NEVER SAW WHO SLIPPED
THAT POISON INTO HIS COFFEE.

32:30.339 --> 32:31.950
AND SNUPPY
PROBABLY DIDN'T EITHER.

32:34.039 --> 32:35.649
PEOPLE ARE LIKE DOGS.

32:35.692 --> 32:37.868
THEY RUN WHEN THEY'RE GUILTY.

32:43.570 --> 32:45.441
Narrator:
AND EMERSON COD HAD A PLAN

32:45.485 --> 32:48.140
FOR HOW TO GET
THEIR "GUILTY DOG" TO RUN.

32:48.183 --> 32:49.837
ALL RIGHT,
LET'S GET HIM READY.

32:52.144 --> 32:53.449
HERE.

32:53.493 --> 32:57.149
ONE LAST TOUCH
WITHOUT TOUCHING HIM.

32:57.192 --> 32:59.803
WOULD YOU PROP HIM UP? HE LOOK
LIKE A WINO ON NEW YEAR'S.

32:59.847 --> 33:00.804
[ CHUCKLES ]

33:00.848 --> 33:03.198
[ GRUNTS ]

33:06.810 --> 33:08.029
DIGBY, STAY.

33:08.073 --> 33:09.117
[ WHIMPERS ]

33:30.486 --> 33:33.011
Which way?[ Mumbling ] OVER THERE.

33:33.054 --> 33:35.013
GET OUT OF THE WAY.
EXCUSE ME.

33:40.018 --> 33:42.846
Minister: SIT.

33:42.890 --> 33:45.545
AND NOW HAROLD'S SWEET WIVES

33:45.588 --> 33:47.808
WOULD EACH LIKE
TO SAY A FEW WORDS.

33:47.851 --> 33:51.116
HAROLD WAS...ONE OF A KIND.

33:51.159 --> 33:53.901
KIND-HEARTED, SWEET.

33:53.944 --> 33:55.642
SWEET SMILE.

33:55.685 --> 33:58.732
FULL OF THE ENDLESS LOVE
OF CHAMPIONING...

33:58.775 --> 34:01.691
CHAMPIONS. HE WAS...

34:01.735 --> 34:04.259
Narrator: EMERSON COD
WAS NOT A RELIGIOUS MAN,

34:04.303 --> 34:06.653
BUT SITTING IN CHURCH,
HE FOUND HIMSELF PRAYING

34:06.696 --> 34:09.612
THAT AGAINST ALL EVIDENCE
TO THE CONTRARY,

34:09.656 --> 34:13.312
SIMONE HUNDIN WAS NOT
A HUSBAND-KILLER.

34:13.355 --> 34:15.053
ALL RIGHT, ON MY MARK.

34:17.359 --> 34:19.840
MARK.

34:19.883 --> 34:21.233
THAT MEANS NOW.

34:24.453 --> 34:26.064
THIS WOULDN'T BE
MYFUNERAL, WOULD IT?

34:27.587 --> 34:29.719
YOU'RE SUPPOSED TO BE DEAD.

34:31.025 --> 34:33.288
AAH!

34:33.332 --> 34:35.029
AAH!AAH!
AAH!AAH!

34:35.073 --> 34:37.379
YOU GOT A MINT? I GOT
THE NASTIEST TASTE IN MY MO--

34:38.728 --> 34:40.469
CAN YOU TAKE CARE OF THAT?YEAH.

34:46.301 --> 34:48.086
[ DIGBY BARKING ]

34:53.091 --> 34:55.310
SIC HER, BOYS!

34:59.140 --> 35:00.446
AAH!

35:01.186 --> 35:02.665
[ DIGBY BARKING ]

35:02.709 --> 35:03.710
OH!

35:05.799 --> 35:08.410
Narrator:
THE FACTS WERE THESE --

35:08.454 --> 35:10.978
WHEN HILARY BECAME
HAROLD HUNDIN'S ONE AND ONLY,

35:11.021 --> 35:12.806
SHE THOUGHT
SHE HAD THE DREAM LIFE.

35:12.849 --> 35:15.504
BUT ADDING THREE MORE
"ONE AND ONLYs"

35:15.548 --> 35:17.898
WAS HAROLD'S IDEA
OF A DREAM LIFE.

35:17.941 --> 35:21.597
SHE FOUND NEW SATISFACTION
AS HER PENTAGONAL UNION

35:21.641 --> 35:25.035
PRODUCED THE WORLD'S
MOST PERFECT DOG, BUBBLEGUM,

35:25.079 --> 35:29.388
WHO WAS TRULY ONE OF A KIND AND
THE CHILD SHE HAD ALWAYS WANTED.

35:29.431 --> 35:32.217
BUT HAROLD HUNDIN HAD OTHER
PLANS FOR BUBBLEGUM.

35:32.260 --> 35:34.915
SHE WOULD BE BROUGHT
TO LIVING ROOMS EVERYWHERE

35:34.958 --> 35:37.831
VIA THE NATIONWIDE CHAIN
OF SNUPPY'S PUPPIES.

35:37.874 --> 35:42.444
EVERYONE, HE BELIEVED, DESERVED
TO HAVE MAN'S BEST BEST FRIEND.

35:42.488 --> 35:44.620
HOWEVER, WHEN HE TOLD
HIS FIRST WIFE, HILARY,

35:44.664 --> 35:47.319
OF HIS PLANS TO CLONE
THEIR PRIZED PUP,

35:47.362 --> 35:50.365
HER REACTION
WAS ANYTHING BUT PERFECT.

35:50.409 --> 35:53.412
HE HAD MADE HIS DECISION,
HAROLD TOLD HER.

35:53.455 --> 35:56.589
BUBBLEGUM WOULD BE
THE CANINE OF THE FUTURE.

35:56.632 --> 35:58.765
SO HILARY MADE HEROWN DECISION.

35:58.808 --> 36:00.723
REFUSING TO SUBJECT HER BABY

36:00.767 --> 36:03.509
TO THE SAME
TORTUROUS SHARED EXISTENCE

36:03.552 --> 36:05.467
SHE HAD BEEN CURSED TO LIVE,

36:05.511 --> 36:09.602
HILARY POISONED HAROLD AND
FRAMED HALLIE TO TAKE ANY FALL,

36:09.645 --> 36:14.694
KNOWING GOOD HALLIE SERVED BUT
DID NOT DRINK CAFFEINE HERSELF.

36:14.737 --> 36:17.262
CAREFUL, SWEETIE.
IT'S HOT.

36:30.188 --> 36:32.233
Narrator: BUT WHAT
THE HUNDIN WIVES LEARNED

36:32.277 --> 36:33.887
UPON THEIR HUSBAND'S DEATH

36:33.930 --> 36:36.585
WAS THAT HAROLD HAD ALREADY
SIGNED THE CONTRACT.

36:39.066 --> 36:43.244
SNUPPY OWNED BUBBLEGUM,
DEAD OR ALIVE.

36:43.288 --> 36:45.115
SNUPPY CAN CLONE BUBBLEGUM?

36:45.159 --> 36:47.379
Narrator:
FOR HILARY, HEARING FROM OLIVE

36:47.422 --> 36:50.295
THAT SNUPPY COULD CLONE
THE CHILD SHE THOUGHT DECEASED

36:50.338 --> 36:51.513
WAS TOO MUCH TO BEAR.

36:51.557 --> 36:53.036
OVER HIS DEAD BODY,

36:53.080 --> 36:55.909
BUBBLEGUM WOULD REMAIN UNIQUE
AT ALL COSTS.

36:55.952 --> 36:57.258
WHAT HILARY DID NOT KNOW

36:57.302 --> 36:59.347
WAS HER MULTIPLE MURDERS
WERE FOR NAUGHT,

36:59.391 --> 37:00.827
AS SISTER-WIFE SIMONE

37:00.870 --> 37:03.264
HAD SECRETLY
FAKED BUBBLEGUM'S DEATH

37:03.308 --> 37:05.571
THE SAME MORNING
HILARY TOOK IT UPON HERSELF

37:05.614 --> 37:07.616
TO POISON THEIR HUSBAND.

37:07.660 --> 37:09.444
Emerson: IF YOU KNEW
YOU WASN'T GUILTY,

37:09.488 --> 37:11.533
WHY YOU ACT LIKE
SOMEBODY WHO WAS?TO PROTECT BUBBLEGUM.

37:11.577 --> 37:13.753
THE ONLY WAY TO KILL
HIS DEAL WITH SNUPPY
WAS TO KILL BUBBLEGUM.

37:13.796 --> 37:14.971
SO YOU FAKED HER DEATH.

37:15.015 --> 37:16.321
BUT SNUPPY THREW YOU
A CURVE BALL

37:16.364 --> 37:17.757
WHEN HE SHOWED YOU
THAT CONTRACT

37:17.800 --> 37:19.585
THAT SAID THAT BUBBLEGUM
WAS HIS, DEAD OR ALIVE.

37:19.628 --> 37:20.977
THAT WAS A SURPRISE.

37:21.021 --> 37:23.632
I DIDN'T KNOW HE COULD
CLONE A DEAD DOG.

37:23.676 --> 37:25.025
BUT I'M SURE HE WAS SURPRISED

37:25.068 --> 37:27.114
WHEN HE DISCOVERED
THE ASHES I TURNED OVER

37:27.157 --> 37:29.290
WERE NOTHING BUT A RAT
BUBBLEGUM HAD CAUGHT.

37:29.334 --> 37:30.291
SLICK.

37:30.335 --> 37:32.815
YOU DON'T KNOW SLICK.

37:36.210 --> 37:37.864
MM-HMM.

37:45.741 --> 37:48.527
I WISH I FELT MORE HEROIC
TACKLING A WOMAN HALF MY SIZE.

37:48.570 --> 37:50.964
YOU BROUGHT HER DOWN.
SHE WAS YOUR BABY ZEBRA.

37:51.007 --> 37:53.532
OR MAYBE SHE WAS THE LION WHO
HAD THE BABY ZEBRA IN HER MAW,

37:53.575 --> 37:55.795
AND YOU WERE THE CROCODILE
THAT CAME FROM NOWHERE.

37:55.838 --> 37:58.319
I DON'T LIKE THE IDEA
OF BEING A CROCODILE,

37:58.363 --> 38:01.104
BUT I GUESS SO LONG
AS THE BABY ZEBRA GOT AWAY.

38:01.148 --> 38:04.760
I'M GONNA HUG DIGBY
AND PRETEND THAT HE'S YOU.

38:09.896 --> 38:13.247
Narrator:
THE PIE MAKER WAS SADDENED
THAT CHUCK COULD HOLD DIGBY

38:13.291 --> 38:17.338
WHILE HE HAD NO ONE,
SAVE THE WAITRESS,

38:17.382 --> 38:21.516
WHO HE NOW REALIZED
HE DID NOT WANT TO HOLD.

38:21.560 --> 38:23.039
NOT IN THAT WAY.

38:23.083 --> 38:24.040
OLIVE?

38:24.084 --> 38:25.433
STILL HERE.

38:25.477 --> 38:26.913
I'M SORRY
I'VE BEEN AVOIDING YOU,

38:26.956 --> 38:30.656
AND I'M SORRY I SAID
OUR SALIVA WASN'T COMPATIBLE.

38:30.699 --> 38:33.311
I'M A BIG GIRL.
I'LL BE OKAY.

38:33.354 --> 38:34.921
I KNOW YOU WILL.

38:34.964 --> 38:36.401
WILL YOU?

38:38.228 --> 38:41.928
HOW WILL YOU EVER KNOW
IF YOUR SALIVA'S COMPATIBLE

38:41.971 --> 38:44.365
UNLESS YOU KISS HER
KISS HER?

38:44.409 --> 38:46.628
I ALREADY KNOW.
I THINK I KNOW.

38:46.672 --> 38:50.371
NO, I KNOW OR I WILL KNOW.

38:50.415 --> 38:52.895
JUST TAKES TIME.

38:52.939 --> 38:54.549
TIME CAN TAKE FOREVER.

38:55.898 --> 38:58.727
I HOPE YOU AND CHUCK
MAKE IT WORK.

38:58.771 --> 39:00.207
I REALLY DO.

39:00.250 --> 39:01.948
IF YOU CAN'T,

39:01.991 --> 39:04.124
I HOPE IT DOESN'T TAKE FOREVER
TO FIGURE THAT OUT.

39:12.306 --> 39:14.221
I JUST
WANT YOU TO BE HAPPY.

39:14.264 --> 39:15.831
Narrator: AND OLIVE DID,

39:15.875 --> 39:18.443
THOUGH SHE WAS NOT YET READY
TO LET GO OF THE HOPE

39:18.486 --> 39:21.402
THAT HER PERFECT PIE MAKER'S
PERFECT HAPPINESS

39:21.446 --> 39:22.838
MIGHT LIE WITH HER.

39:22.882 --> 39:24.884
NIGHT.
YEAH.

39:25.798 --> 39:29.149
Narrator:
AS THE PIE MAKER PONDERED
THE HAND THAT HE JUST HELD,

39:29.192 --> 39:33.719
HE BEGAN TO UNDERSTAND THE MANY
DIFFERENT FORMS LOVE COULD TAKE,

39:33.762 --> 39:36.809
EACH ONE PRECIOUS
IN ITS OWN WAY.

39:38.811 --> 39:41.422
AW. THANKS.

39:41.466 --> 39:45.774
Narrator: THOUGH SOME
WERE MORE UNIQUE THAN OTHERS.

39:48.124 --> 39:50.779
YOU'RE THE ONLY ONE FOR ME.

39:50.823 --> 39:54.479
I KNOW
YOU FEEL THAT NOW, BUT...

39:54.522 --> 39:58.352
THERE ARE THINGS YOU WANT.

39:58.396 --> 40:00.354
THERE ARE THINGS
WE BOTH WANT.

40:00.398 --> 40:02.225
SO?
EVERYONE WANTS STUFF.

40:02.269 --> 40:04.227
WE WAKE UP EVERY DAY
WITH A LIST OF WISHES
A MILE LONG,

40:04.271 --> 40:07.143
AND MAYBE WE SPEND
OUR LIVES TRYING TO MAKE
THOSE WISHES COME TRUE.

40:07.187 --> 40:09.450
BUT...JUST BECAUSE
WE WANTTHEM

40:09.494 --> 40:11.844
DOESN'T MEAN WE NEEDTHEM
TO BE HAPPY.

40:13.367 --> 40:18.894
WHAT DO YOU NEED
TO BE HAPPY?

40:22.202 --> 40:22.768
YOU.
